1
00:00:50,780 --> 00:00:55,740
=Sugar and Lies=
(A Different Her: The Women's Trilogy)

2
00:00:56,820 --> 00:00:59,780
=Episode 4=
=Kiss You at Sunrise=

3
00:01:03,480 --> 00:01:04,520
Had enough to eat?

4
00:01:08,280 --> 00:01:09,240
Want another bowl?

5
00:01:12,240 --> 00:01:13,080
Sure.

6
00:01:13,520 --> 00:01:15,400
Let's pack up and head back soon.

7
00:01:17,800 --> 00:01:19,120
Not staying here tonight?

8
00:01:19,640 --> 00:01:20,680
You actually want to stay?

9
00:01:23,640 --> 00:01:24,640
There are mosquitoes.

10
00:01:25,280 --> 00:01:26,220
Aren't you scared?

11
00:01:35,520 --> 00:01:36,360
Alright.

12
00:01:36,760 --> 00:01:37,800
Stop messing around.

13
00:01:38,400 --> 00:01:39,240
Let's go home.

14
00:01:51,800 --> 00:01:53,160
I'm not joking.

15
00:01:55,080 --> 00:01:56,600
I really don't want to leave.

16
00:02:03,840 --> 00:02:05,280
(Sorry, Boss)

17
00:02:05,280 --> 00:02:06,880
(Your Keep Love shows)

18
00:02:06,880 --> 00:02:09,000
(this is the best way
to boost the Romance Score)

19
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:11,040
(and to catch the sunrise on time.)

20
00:02:15,640 --> 00:02:17,520
You don't think it's too cramped in here?

21
00:02:20,920 --> 00:02:22,840
Just one night.

22
00:02:23,360 --> 00:02:24,200
What's wrong?

23
00:02:24,520 --> 00:02:26,080
Planning to play soccer in there?

24
00:02:38,600 --> 00:02:39,720
There's a snake!

25
00:02:41,560 --> 00:02:42,400
Where?

26
00:02:45,600 --> 00:02:46,440
Just kidding.

27
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:53,400
Alright, it's fine now.

28
00:03:02,880 --> 00:03:03,720
Aming.

29
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:07,000
You seem…

30
00:03:08,840 --> 00:03:10,320
actually a bit different.

31
00:03:12,400 --> 00:03:13,480
Different how?

32
00:03:15,040 --> 00:03:16,040
Hard to say.

33
00:03:18,240 --> 00:03:19,200
It's just…

34
00:03:20,640 --> 00:03:21,560
a feeling.

35
00:03:23,240 --> 00:03:25,080
Is that good or bad?

36
00:03:27,840 --> 00:03:29,040
I can't tell either.

37
00:03:32,040 --> 00:03:33,200
I'll keep trying.

38
00:03:54,440 --> 00:03:55,280
What's up?

39
00:03:55,640 --> 00:03:57,120
I'm tailing my stepmom.

40
00:03:57,560 --> 00:03:58,800
I think she's seeing someone

41
00:03:58,800 --> 00:04:00,000
behind my dad's back.

42
00:04:01,160 --> 00:04:02,440
I have to find solid proof.

43
00:04:08,840 --> 00:04:09,820
You skipped class again.

44
00:04:11,160 --> 00:04:12,200
How did you know?

45
00:04:12,400 --> 00:04:13,760
Didn't see you at morning exercise.

46
00:04:15,680 --> 00:04:17,360
Studying is just too boring.

47
00:04:19,080 --> 00:04:20,660
I want to watch the stars on Mount Nan.

48
00:04:20,660 --> 00:04:21,600
Want to come with me?

49
00:04:27,160 --> 00:04:28,000
Whatever.

50
00:04:29,640 --> 00:04:30,520
Alright, fair enough.

51
00:04:31,120 --> 00:04:32,640
But you have to agree to one thing.

52
00:04:32,640 --> 00:04:33,480
What thing?

53
00:04:34,880 --> 00:04:35,840
No skipping classes.

54
00:04:37,240 --> 00:04:38,560
And no lying.

55
00:04:39,520 --> 00:04:40,560
What happens if I lie?

56
00:04:41,240 --> 00:04:42,120
If you lie to me...

57
00:04:43,920 --> 00:04:44,840
If you lie to me,

58
00:04:45,080 --> 00:04:46,320
we're not friends anymore.

59
00:04:47,040 --> 00:04:48,280
Alright, no lies.

60
00:04:48,880 --> 00:04:50,120
So, that means you'll come.

61
00:04:57,540 --> 00:04:59,980
(Utopia)

62
00:05:07,520 --> 00:05:08,360
Miss Gu.

63
00:05:08,520 --> 00:05:10,080
Let's go over tomorrow's script.

64
00:05:10,680 --> 00:05:11,680
Mr. Zhou,

65
00:05:12,080 --> 00:05:14,840
I don't work outside work hours.

66
00:05:16,240 --> 00:05:18,400
Then can we make this your...

67
00:05:18,400 --> 00:05:19,640
dating time?

68
00:05:20,840 --> 00:05:22,720
A straight pitch
can still be a bad shot.

69
00:05:23,120 --> 00:05:24,120
Take it easy.

70
00:05:25,040 --> 00:05:26,720
You're not worried about
your best friend?

71
00:05:27,040 --> 00:05:28,440
If you have that much energy,

72
00:05:28,440 --> 00:05:30,480
you should be more concerned about Boss.

73
00:05:30,800 --> 00:05:31,640
Yeah.

74
00:05:31,960 --> 00:05:32,800
True enough.

75
00:05:33,400 --> 00:05:35,080
Neither of them is easy to handle.

76
00:05:35,520 --> 00:05:36,440
I really hope

77
00:05:36,440 --> 00:05:37,800
their back-and-forth

78
00:05:37,800 --> 00:05:38,720
lasts a bit longer.

79
00:05:39,120 --> 00:05:39,960
That way,

80
00:05:40,280 --> 00:05:41,800
my stay in Mancheng

81
00:05:41,800 --> 00:05:42,880
will be extended.

82
00:05:48,200 --> 00:05:49,040
Cheers.

83
00:05:52,360 --> 00:05:54,120
Alcohol, at the right moment,

84
00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:56,960
can totally boost emotions
through the roof.

85
00:05:57,560 --> 00:05:59,560
But your Keep Love didn't tell you that

86
00:06:00,040 --> 00:06:02,560
it only works
if both people feel the spark.

87
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:12,840
You feel it yet?

88
00:06:13,280 --> 00:06:14,400
Childish.

89
00:06:16,280 --> 00:06:17,120
Stupid.

90
00:06:25,600 --> 00:06:27,000
Boss, what's the Wi-Fi password?

91
00:06:27,220 --> 00:06:30,740
(Forget It Bar. Note: No Wi-Fi here,
phones get no signal.)

92
00:06:32,520 --> 00:06:34,360
With that setup,
do you even get customers?

93
00:06:35,520 --> 00:06:36,640
Aren't you a customer?

94
00:06:36,640 --> 00:06:38,000
How am I supposed to pay later?

95
00:06:44,160 --> 00:06:45,640
It's fine, on the house.

96
00:06:47,680 --> 00:06:49,400
Is this place some kind of charity?

97
00:06:51,360 --> 00:06:52,200
Depends who asks.

98
00:06:56,440 --> 00:06:58,280
Do I look broke to you?

99
00:07:00,200 --> 00:07:01,040
You look cool.

100
00:07:02,760 --> 00:07:05,000
Has anyone told you
you're kind of pretentious?

101
00:07:21,400 --> 00:07:22,760
You scared me half to death.

102
00:07:23,400 --> 00:07:24,880
I thought you'd fallen asleep.

103
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:27,080
Why don't we

104
00:07:27,520 --> 00:07:28,680
sleep a bit longer?

105
00:07:29,320 --> 00:07:30,200
Hand me the phone.

106
00:07:32,120 --> 00:07:33,100
If you keep making noise,

107
00:07:33,100 --> 00:07:33,840
I'm going to…

108
00:07:42,400 --> 00:07:43,240
Aming,

109
00:07:43,880 --> 00:07:46,000
do you remember

110
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:48,960
that summer
when I'd just gotten into college?

111
00:07:48,960 --> 00:07:51,480
We snuck away to travel together.

112
00:07:52,080 --> 00:07:53,280
I couldn't bring myself to

113
00:07:53,280 --> 00:07:54,840
spend the money you earned from working.

114
00:07:55,730 --> 00:07:56,600
So we took

115
00:07:56,600 --> 00:07:58,560
that green train for hours and hours.

116
00:07:59,600 --> 00:08:01,240
It was exhausting.

117
00:08:01,760 --> 00:08:03,000
I even twisted my ankle.

118
00:08:03,880 --> 00:08:05,800
You carried me around for a few days.

119
00:08:07,200 --> 00:08:09,680
You carried me everywhere.

120
00:08:10,520 --> 00:08:12,080
Even to watch the sunrise.

121
00:08:13,480 --> 00:08:14,760
Back then, you told me,

122
00:08:15,480 --> 00:08:16,800
you'd always keep me safe.

123
00:08:18,240 --> 00:08:19,640
Do you still remember that?

124
00:08:30,280 --> 00:08:31,220
Later on, I studied hard

125
00:08:32,480 --> 00:08:34,840
and got into a university in Mancheng.

126
00:08:36,440 --> 00:08:38,160
I thought moving to Mancheng

127
00:08:39,560 --> 00:08:41,440
meant we could be together forever.

128
00:08:42,400 --> 00:08:44,320
I thought I could leave that home behind

129
00:08:45,520 --> 00:08:47,040
and never look back.

130
00:08:48,320 --> 00:08:49,840
But I didn't expect

131
00:08:51,440 --> 00:08:53,160
you'd walk away halfway through.

132
00:08:54,920 --> 00:08:56,400
Years have passed since then,

133
00:08:58,480 --> 00:09:00,080
and it's still just me,

134
00:09:02,400 --> 00:09:04,600
going in circles, stuck in the same place.

135
00:09:06,840 --> 00:09:09,120
The truth is, being with Hu Yitong

136
00:09:10,240 --> 00:09:12,360
was about fulfilling my dad's last wish.

137
00:09:15,040 --> 00:09:16,400
Only by getting married

138
00:09:17,200 --> 00:09:18,560
could I receive the inheritance.

139
00:09:19,920 --> 00:09:21,560
I really waited for you a long time

140
00:09:24,320 --> 00:09:25,760
until six months ago.

141
00:09:27,240 --> 00:09:28,720
I just told myself,

142
00:09:29,360 --> 00:09:30,400
it's time to let go.

143
00:09:33,600 --> 00:09:34,680
Aming,

144
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:37,880
tell me,

145
00:09:39,920 --> 00:09:42,320
why couldn't you come back earlier?

146
00:09:52,280 --> 00:09:53,520
Honestly,

147
00:09:53,520 --> 00:09:55,280
you're all passion and fire,

148
00:09:55,280 --> 00:09:56,840
while she's calm as still water.

149
00:09:57,360 --> 00:09:58,640
Maybe you should just let it go.

150
00:09:59,560 --> 00:10:01,320
This might have gone wrong.

151
00:10:01,880 --> 00:10:03,520
Why can't people just believe

152
00:10:03,520 --> 00:10:05,480
what's right in front of them?

153
00:10:05,480 --> 00:10:06,300
But Keep Love showed

154
00:10:06,300 --> 00:10:07,840
(Success Rate)
the success rate is 99%.

155
00:10:08,040 --> 00:10:10,760
Too bad you're that unlucky one percent.

156
00:10:11,320 --> 00:10:13,040
Then create an exclusive strategy for me.

157
00:10:13,040 --> 00:10:14,040
I have to win her over.

158
00:10:14,680 --> 00:10:15,960
Boss will go after you.

159
00:10:16,120 --> 00:10:17,120
As part of the deal,

160
00:10:17,560 --> 00:10:19,120
I'll keep quiet about you liking Boss.

161
00:10:19,520 --> 00:10:20,600
Plus two more grand.

162
00:10:21,280 --> 00:10:22,800
So what if I like him?

163
00:10:22,800 --> 00:10:24,120
I don't need him to feel the same.

164
00:10:28,080 --> 00:10:28,900
Then how about this?

165
00:10:28,900 --> 00:10:30,190
(Checked the screen 10 times in 5 mins)

166
00:10:31,820 --> 00:10:34,460
(Admiration Rate: 70%)

167
00:10:38,160 --> 00:10:39,960
- Had fun?
- It was okay.

168
00:10:39,960 --> 00:10:41,560
Don't forget why you're back to Mancheng.

169
00:10:41,560 --> 00:10:42,440
It's not for love,

170
00:10:42,720 --> 00:10:43,600
but for work.

171
00:10:44,280 --> 00:10:45,440
And don't you forget,

172
00:10:46,600 --> 00:10:47,760
livestreaming is your job,

173
00:10:48,600 --> 00:10:49,660
not a company-funded date.

174
00:10:49,920 --> 00:10:50,840
Boss.

175
00:10:50,840 --> 00:10:52,560
Did you find something?

176
00:10:53,520 --> 00:10:54,560
Numbers don't lie.

177
00:10:55,640 --> 00:10:56,760
I'll say this once.

178
00:11:11,240 --> 00:11:12,080
What's wrong?

179
00:11:17,960 --> 00:11:19,600
I thought you ditched me.

180
00:11:20,760 --> 00:11:21,600
Why would I?

181
00:11:22,520 --> 00:11:23,640
My phone's dead.

182
00:11:24,640 --> 00:11:25,560
Grab a charger.

183
00:11:27,760 --> 00:11:28,800
It's not time yet.

184
00:11:28,800 --> 00:11:29,720
You can't leave.

185
00:11:41,320 --> 00:11:42,340
You're not letting me go.

186
00:11:43,200 --> 00:11:44,040
Then I'm staying.

187
00:12:00,240 --> 00:12:02,320
Crazy that we looped all the way back here.

188
00:12:05,520 --> 00:12:07,120
The weather today…

189
00:12:07,120 --> 00:12:08,560
We probably won't see the sunrise.

190
00:12:12,200 --> 00:12:13,240
If you don't believe me,

191
00:12:13,760 --> 00:12:14,640
let's make a bet.

192
00:12:16,400 --> 00:12:17,240
What's the bet?

193
00:12:17,960 --> 00:12:18,920
If...

194
00:12:19,640 --> 00:12:21,000
the sun does rise,

195
00:12:21,000 --> 00:12:22,000
you give me a kiss.

196
00:12:22,520 --> 00:12:23,760
And if it doesn't?

197
00:12:24,480 --> 00:12:26,080
Then I'll kiss you instead.

198
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:28,960
You're so silly.

199
00:12:30,720 --> 00:12:31,680
Do you remember

200
00:12:32,080 --> 00:12:33,840
that time we went to see the sunrise?

201
00:12:33,840 --> 00:12:34,880
You couldn't even get up.

202
00:12:35,360 --> 00:12:36,440
And your leg was hurt.

203
00:12:37,520 --> 00:12:39,240
I wrapped you in my coat,

204
00:12:39,240 --> 00:12:40,880
carried you all the way up the mountain.

205
00:12:43,040 --> 00:12:44,600
That path was so rough.

206
00:12:45,300 --> 00:12:46,800
You said we wouldn't make it in time.

207
00:12:47,880 --> 00:12:50,000
But we still made it before sunrise.

208
00:12:56,440 --> 00:12:57,740
So the things I said last night,

209
00:12:57,740 --> 00:12:58,640
you heard them all?

210
00:13:05,120 --> 00:13:06,000
What did you say?

211
00:13:07,240 --> 00:13:08,200
The wind was too loud.

212
00:13:14,640 --> 00:13:15,480
Look!

213
00:13:16,200 --> 00:13:17,400
The sunrise!

214
00:13:19,830 --> 00:13:22,270
♪That song suddenly started playing♪

215
00:13:22,890 --> 00:13:25,230
♪And I thought of you again♪

216
00:13:25,880 --> 00:13:30,930
♪Even though I swore to the world
we were done♪

217
00:13:31,880 --> 00:13:34,520
♪All my friends laughed at me♪

218
00:13:34,820 --> 00:13:36,820
♪Why can't I just let it go♪

219
00:13:36,840 --> 00:13:38,480
If you bet, you take the loss.

220
00:13:39,200 --> 00:13:43,130
♪But how could they ever know
how good you were to me♪

221
00:13:43,510 --> 00:13:46,600
♪I'm falling into
the swamp of your charm♪

222
00:13:46,850 --> 00:13:49,210
♪It's painful yet feels so right♪

223
00:13:49,320 --> 00:13:50,440
Give and take, that's fair.

224
00:13:50,440 --> 00:13:52,160
♪As the endless night unfolds♪

225
00:13:52,160 --> 00:13:54,830
♪I toss and turn, can't fall asleep♪

226
00:13:56,620 --> 00:13:59,750
♪You keep running through my mind♪

227
00:13:59,750 --> 00:14:02,820
♪Nothing matters more than you♪

228
00:14:03,130 --> 00:14:04,320
♪Why?♪

229
00:14:04,680 --> 00:14:08,420
♪You walked out of my world♪

230
00:14:09,680 --> 00:14:10,760
Does it look good?

231
00:14:11,780 --> 00:14:14,880
♪Can you give me one more hug?♪

232
00:14:16,710 --> 00:14:21,120
♪Did you hear me say please don't go♪

233
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:24,520
Remember what's worth remembering.

234
00:14:24,880 --> 00:14:26,280
Forget what needs to be let go.

235
00:14:26,800 --> 00:14:27,840
Change what you can change.

236
00:14:27,840 --> 00:14:28,680
Accept

237
00:14:29,040 --> 00:14:29,980
what can't be changed.

238
00:14:30,200 --> 00:14:31,480
But this is your life.

239
00:14:32,000 --> 00:14:33,040
So why can't you make

240
00:14:33,040 --> 00:14:34,080
the choices you truly want?

241
00:14:34,080 --> 00:14:34,920
And what about yours?

242
00:14:34,930 --> 00:14:36,240
Is your life really what you want?

243
00:14:36,640 --> 00:14:37,920
Do you truly not like it

244
00:14:39,000 --> 00:14:40,360
or do you want to forget the past?

245
00:14:41,520 --> 00:14:42,480
No need to thank me.

246
00:14:43,080 --> 00:14:44,320
It's just a contract.

247
00:14:44,440 --> 00:14:45,360
It will get expired.

248
00:14:45,360 --> 00:14:46,600
What if I want to renew it?

249
00:15:14,010 --> 00:15:21,010
♪I forgot this is a movie meant for one♪

250
00:15:25,410 --> 00:15:32,770
♪Somehow you're still here,
crying with me♪

251
00:15:37,220 --> 00:15:39,160
♪They say♪

252
00:15:39,570 --> 00:15:47,950
♪Lovers should never hold hands
while watching a sad movie♪

253
00:15:48,470 --> 00:15:51,450
♪Some endings cannot be changed♪

254
00:15:51,670 --> 00:15:57,620
♪They don't belong in sweet memories♪

255
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:04,760
♪I've already lost you♪

256
00:16:04,760 --> 00:16:10,240
♪Thinking of it takes my breath away♪

257
00:16:10,540 --> 00:16:16,490
♪The movie ends, so many couples around♪

258
00:16:16,490 --> 00:16:21,270
♪Yet none were ever like us♪

259
00:16:22,380 --> 00:16:26,410
♪The past will always pass♪

260
00:16:26,740 --> 00:16:34,320
♪If you could still hold me tight
in your arms♪

261
00:16:34,790 --> 00:16:38,040
♪I'd believe
that there are miracles in love♪

262
00:16:38,600 --> 00:16:44,250
♪I'd prove
that I'm still in love with you♪

263
00:16:46,710 --> 00:16:50,240
♪I've learned how to cherish
what we had♪

264
00:16:50,240 --> 00:16:56,500
♪But sadly, it's not you♪
